"'''The Capture of Imperial Hazard'''" is a short story written by [[Nora Mayers]] and illustrated by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 10|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 10]] by [[West End Games]] in [[May]] [[1996]] and was later archived online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[July 9]], [[2007]].

==Plot summary==
[[Sayer Mon Neela]], former assistant [[Barrister|barrister]] [[General/Legends|general]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]], now a war strategist and high-[[Military rank/Legends|ranking]] [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|rebel]] leader, was located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Horob]]. As [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces converged on the primitive planet, rebel base hurried to evacuate. To buy the ground forces time to escape, Neela ordered her [[Yacht/Legends|yacht]] the ''[[Starcrossed]]'' to, instead of making a jump to the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Rim]], intercept the incoming [[Victory-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Victory''-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Imperial Hazard]]''.

Neela then opened a channel to the Star Destroyer, identified herself and requested to meet the [[Captain/Legends|captain]]. To ensure her safety, she threatened to self-destruct her yatch and blow the ''Imperial Hazard'' at the first sign of aggression. To capture the wanted rebel leader, the Star Destroyer's captain [[Sergus Lanox]] accepted Neela to his ship. During the two's private meeting, they glimpsed into each other's character and developed mutual admiration, which they tried to mask. As Lanox attempted to capture Neela, she threatened to destroy ''Imperial Hazard'' with the ''Starcrossed'', and counterofferred Lanox to surrender his ship to the Alliance. As the negotiation became a stalemate, Lanox had Neela escorted back to her ship. Unbeknownst to Lanox, Neela had secretly taken aboard a prototype [[Spy/Legends|spy]] device developed by rebel [[Scientist/Legends|scientists]] on Horob. The device decoded the encryption of all systems on the ''Imperial Hazard'', and started to cause critical system failures as it overloaded the Star Destroyer's [[Computer/Legends|computers]]. Soon the ''Imperial Hazard'' started to lose altitude, dragging ''Starcrossed'' with it as they were connected by an umbilical. 

Discovering Neela's treachery, Lanox personally led a [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] contingent to storm the corridor. As the Imperial captain and the rebel leader confronted each other in a firefight, the ''Imperial Hazard'' imploded, rocking the corridor and plunged Lanox into Neela's arms. The two fell onto the floor, dazed and gaping. In the moment of [[Living Force/Legends|life]] and [[Death/Legends|death]], Lanox abandoned the last chance to [[Prison/Legends|arrest]] the [[Gender/Legends|woman]]. He helped Neela to escaped by opening the jammed hatch on her ship, and gave her a long kiss, before struggling back to his own ship through the rapidly depressurizing corridor. Back to safety in a rebel base on [[Carosi XII]], Neela privately admitted her admiration for Lanox to [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] general [[Polo Se'lab|Se'lab]] before the celebration held for her. Later through [[HoloNet News/Legends|holonet news]], Neela witnessed Sergus Lanox being presented the [[Distinguished Medal of Imperial Honor/Legends|Distinguished Medal of Imperial Honor]] by [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Miltin Takel|Takel]], for his extreme heroism against rebel [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorism]].

